-- Intesa Sanpaolo names new chief operating officer
-- By Danilo Masoni
-- Wed May 14, 2014 07:22AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, May 14 (Reuters) - Intesa Sanpaolo <ISP.MI> has named insider Eliano Omar Lodesani as its new chief operating officer, Italy's largest retail bank said in a statement on Wednesday.

Lodesani has been with the banking group for several years and is head of its regional centre of the Veneto, Friuli Venezia Giulia and Trentino Alto Adige regions, which has 724 branches.